      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Aaron Bohrod (1907-1992) was an American realist painter and a participant in the Federal Art Project and the 
U.S. Army War Unit's project on the pictorial history of World War II.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Harold Schatzberg Collection relating to Aaron Bohrod</emph> contains correspondence, 
clippings, exhibit notices, and other items relating to painter Aaron Bohrod.  Clippings include the LIFE magazine cover 
featuring Bohrod, from April 30, 1945.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Material is subdivided into correspondence and other material; no particular arrangement.</p>
      </arrangement>
      
      <relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1">
